<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="Aink144-kilavi">
        talaimakaṉ varaintu kōṭal niṉaiyātu kaḷavoḻukkamē virumpi oḻukāniṉṟā ṉeṉpatu aṟintu vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaḷ, ‘avaṉ kūṟiyavāṟṟāl iṉi kaṭitiṉ varaivaṉ; āṟṟāyākātoḻiyavēṇṭum’ eṉṟa tōḻikkuc colliyatu</p>    <p xml:lang="en">
         Spoken by the heroine who changed [her mind], having known that the hero, not thinking of providing, having married [her], desiring only a secret relationship, behaves thus, to the confidante who said ‘Because of the way he spoke/promised, he will marry [you] quickly now; it is necessary to behave without getting impatient’.
 
 </p>
 </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink144">
<l>ekkar ñāḻa liṇarpaṭu potumpart</l>
<l>taṉikkuru kuṟaṅkun tuṟaivaṟ</l>
<l>kiṉippacan taṉṟeṉ māmaik kaviṉē</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
  <l>My dark beauty has now become pale</l>
  <l>For the man from the ghat in which the single wader bird slumbers alone</l>
    <l>On a branch of the Ñāḻal tree on the dune, from which clusters fall. </l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
